'''Tizmekt tazegzawt''' neɣ '''Taɣaɣa tazegzawt'''' ([[Assaɣ ussnan]]: '''Balaenoptera musculus''') d [[aɣersiw]] [[Timsuṭaṭ tiwlalin|amsuṭaṭ awlal]] meqqren s waṭas yeṭṭafar [[Tader-fesna]] n [[tilekkmanin|tzemkin tibalinyin]],<ref name="factsheet">[https://web.archive.org/web/20070711025158/http://www.acsonline.org/factpack/bluewhl.htm American Cetacean Society Fact Sheet – Blue Whales]. Archived from the original on 11 July 2007. Retrieved 20 June 2007</ref>Teɣzi-ynes yessaweṭen ɣer 30 m<ref>J. Calambokidis and G. Steiger (1998). ''Blue Whales''.Voyageur Press</ref> d [[azuk|wazuk-is]] i zemren ad yugar 170 n [[Ṭunn|iṭunnen]]<ref>[http://nationalzoo.si.edu/Animals/AnimalRecords/ Animal Records]. Smithsonian National Zoological Park. Retrieved 2007-05-29 {{assaɣ yerrẓen|date= yulyu 2017 |bot=JarBot}} {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160229111309/http://nationalzoo.si.edu/Animals/AnimalRecords/ |date=29 fuṛaṛ 2016}} </ref> yeǧǧa-t ad yili d [[Tiddiwin n imuddiren|aɣersiw meqqren yettwassnen]] deg wakuden yakk.<ref>[http://science.howstuffworks.com/zoology/all-about-animals/question687.htm What is the biggest animal ever to exist on Earth?]. How Stuff Works. Retrieved 2007-05-29 {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140224071211/http://science.howstuffworks.com/zoology/all-about-animals/question687.htm |date=24 fuṛaṛ 2014}}</ref>

Tafekka n tzemket tazegzawt d taɣezfant d tusdidt tettwaklu s waṭas n yiniten ifarayen anda azagur-is d [[azunɣid]] yezzegzun ma deg yidis n wadda d adnanes.<ref>[http://www.fao.org/fishery/species/2744/en Species Fact Sheets: Balaenoptera musculus (Linnaeus, 1758)]. Fisheries and Aquaculture Department, [[Tuddsa n wučči d temɣigert|Food and Agriculture Organization]], [[Tuddsa n Yeɣlanen Yedduklen|United Nations]]. Retrieved 2012-12-24 {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180203032122/http://www.fao.org/fishery/species/2744/en |date=03 fuṛaṛ 2018}}</ref>

Tizmekt tazegzawt tgebber seg 3 n [[Adu-telmest|tdefrin]] ma drus, Tidefrin-a gant:
* '''B. m. musculus''': tettidir deg ugafa n [[Agaraw anaṭlas|ugaraw anaṭlas]] d ugafa n [[Agaraw Amelwi|ugaraw amelwi]] 
* '''B. m. intermedia''': tettidir deg [[Agaraw anaẓul|ugaraw anaẓul]] 
* '''[[Tizmekt tazegzawt tawezlant|B. m. brevicauda]]''': tettidir deg [[Agaraw Ahendi|ugaraw ahendi]] d unẓul n ugaraw amelwi, yakk d '''B. m. indica''' izemren ad yili d tadfert yeṭṭafaren tadulmest-a

Učči n tzemkin tizegrawin yezzi ɣef [[tiruca|truca]] timeẓẓyanin kan yettusemman s [[tikrileyyin|tekrileyyin]].<ref name="wheelock">Jason de Koning and Geoff Wild (1997). [http://whale.wheelock.edu/bwcontaminants/welcome.html Contaminant analysis of organochlorines in blubber biopsies from blue whales in the St. Lawrence Seaway]. Trent University. Retrieved 2007-06-29 {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170328043530/http://whale.wheelock.edu/bwcontaminants/welcome.html |date=28 meɣres 2017}}</ref>
